Subiculum molecular layer.Definition: Layer of the subiculum characterized by a paucity of cells lying superficial to the subiculum pyramidal cell layer.  It is continuous with the stratum radiaum and stratum moleculare-lacunosum of CA1.  Adapted from Paxinos, G. The rat central nervous system, 2nd ed, Academic Press, San Diego, 1995, pg. 468)
